column6: company_profile

Telenor Group is a multinational telecommunications company. The firm offers fixed-line and mobile telephony, Internet, digital television, and IT services. It is one of the world's largest mobile telecommunications companies with operations in Scandinavia, eastern Europe and Asia. Telenor owns networks in 12 countries, with operations in 29 countries. The company was founded in 1970 and is based in Fornebu in Baerum, Norway.

ABBA Aluminium Co., Ltd. manufactures aluminium and aluminium extruded products. Its products include curtain wall, furnace, aluminium profiles, coating, industrial extrusion, and liquid coating. The company offers services, such as surface treatment, fabrication, aluminium plate processing, curtain wall assembly, and import billets and tensile testing. ABBA Aluminium Co., Ltd. was founded in 2005 and is based in Taoyuan County, Taiwan.
column36: Chen Pai-chin, chairman of ABBA Aluminium, stated that the country's young workforce was one of the reasons for establishing a base in Myanmar.  He added that the presence of a large number of "ethnic Chinese people in Myanmar" gives the country an edge over other CLMV economies (Cambodia, Laos, Myanmar and Vietnam) for manufacturers from Chinese-speaking countries.

column6: Deutsche Risk is involved in security and risk management. The company acts as a consultant to clients and advises them in areas such as security, innovations, digitalization and sustainable life-cycle management. The company was founded in 2017 and is based in Neu-Isenburg, Frankfurt, Germany.

Diethelm Keller Holding, along with its subsidiaries, engages in marketing, brand management, logistics and travel businesses. The company provides sourcing, marketing, sales, distribution and aftersales services. It also offers marketing, brand building and distribution services for medium-sized enterprises. Diethelm Keller Holding was founded in 2000 as a result of a merger between Diethelm and Edward Keller. The company is headquartered in Zurich, Switzerland.

Osotspa Company Limited develops, produces, and distributes speciality drinks that refresh the mind and body of consumers in Thailand and internationally. The company was founded in 1891 and is based in Bangkok, Thailand.

Jardine Matheson Holdings, through its subsidiaries, engages in engineering and construction, transport services, insurance broking, property investment and development, retailing, restaurants, luxury hotels, motor vehicles and related activities, financial services, heavy equipment, mining, and agribusinesses primarily in Greater China and south-east Asia. The company is based in Central, Hong Kong, and was founded in 1832.
column36: Wai Sam Wong, managing director of Myanmar Jardine Schindler Limited. "The training centre demonstrates Schindler's long-term commitment to safety and quality to deliver outstanding customer service through professionally trained technicians. This is the key element in driving sustainable growth in Myanmar."

column6: Modern Energy Management delivers project lifecycle certainty to renewable energy financiers, developers, operators and investors working in rapidly expanding emerging markets. Its team of engineers and project managers develop, construct and deliver complex, profitable projects in remote, rapidly expanding international markets. The firm was founded in 2013 and is based in Singapore.
Daewoo Bus manufactures and distributes buses and bus chassis. It offers complete bus units and self drive away. The company was founded in 2004 and is based in Bucheon, South Korea.

Indian Oil Corporation (IOC), together with its subsidiaries, engages in refining, transporting, and marketing petroleum products in India. It is also involved in the exploration and production of crude oil and gas. The company also exports its products serving the consumer, industrial and marine sectors. The company was founded in 1959 and is based in New Delhi, India.

column4: Mitsubishi HC Capital (Mitsubishi UFJ Lease & Finance)
column6: Mitsubishi UFJ Financial Group is a holding company for the Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ, Mitsubishi UFJ Trust and Banking Corporation, Mitsubishi UFJ Securities Holdings, Mitsubishi UFJ Morgan Stanley Securities, Mitsubishi UFJ NICOS and other companies engaged in a range of financial businesses. Its services include commercial banking, trust banking, securities, credit cards, consumer finance, asset management, leasing and fields of financial services. In May 2010, the company and Morgan Stanley formed two joint ventures in Japan by integrating respective Japanese securities companies engaged in investment banking and securities businesses. Mitsubishi UFJ Financial Group was founded in 2001 and is based in Tokyo, Japan.
column36: The Myanmarese economy continues to grow, backed by factors such as growth in the domestic market with a population of more than 51 million, and geographical advantages of being bordered by neighbouring countries such as China, India, and Thailand

column6: The ASEAN Legal Alliance (ALA) was formed to bring together law firms from each of the 10 member states to provide a truly ASEAN wide legal network. The firm is ASEAN focused on helping its clients to navigate the ASEAN legal landscape. The firm was founded in 2014 and is based in Singapore.

Fast Retailing is an apparel retailer that operates Uniqlo and other brands. The company was formerly known as Ogori Shoji and changed its name to Fast Retailing in September 1991. Fast Retailing is based in Yamaguchi, Japan, and was founded in 1949.
MSN Laboratories operates as a pharmaceutical company. The company offers active pharmaceutical ingredients and finished dosages. It is based in Hyderabad, India.
column37: ASEAN, Africa, Latin America and CIS regions

column6: Kuoni is a tourist travel company. Kuoni was founded in 1906 and is currently headquartered in Zurich, Switzerland.

Electricity Generating Authority of Thailand is engaged in the generation, transmission, and distribution of electricity to distributing authorities, industrial customers, and other utilities in Thailand and internationally. It owns and operates three thermal power plants, six combined cycle power plants, 22 hydropower plants, eight renewable energy power plants, and a diesel power plant. The company also purchases bulk electricity from independent power producers, small power producers, and from neighboring countries, such as Lao PDR and Malaysia. The company was founded in 1969 and is headquartered in Nonthaburi, Thailand.

EV Hive is a co-working and community operator.  It manages more than 30,000 sq m of workspace in 21 locations across Indonesia, with eight additional locations under construction. Besides opening collaborative workspaces, the company also offers a broad suite of supporting services and a community network to support its members in starting and growing their business. The company was founded in 2015 and is based in Jakarta, Indonesia.

Toyo Ink, through its subsidiaries, engages in printing and information, packaging materials, polymers and coatings and colourants and functional materials businesses in Japan and internationally. It manufactures and sells polymer materials, inks, waxes, coating materials, high performance pigments and offset inks. The company also engages in the R&D of polymer designing technology, the sale and servicing of products, the provision of information, system integration and consulting services for printing workflows. In addition, it provides logistics services and engages in the import and sale of pigments, dispersions and specialty chemical products. It trades raw materials, printing equipment and products, operating as an investment holding company. It is also investing in a power plant in Vietnam. The company was established in 1896 and is based in Tokyo, Japan.
column36: In recent years, the government's aggressive policies to attract foreign funding, such as infrastructure enhancements and relaxation of import restrictions, have substantially strengthened Myanmar's investment climate, making it an attractive investment destination, according to Toyo Ink.

column6: Graham Holdings Company, through its subsidiaries, operates as a diversified education and media company worldwide. It provides a range of certificate, diploma, and degree programs, as well as online education services; and test preparation business services in pre-college, graduate, health, and bar review, as well as publishes and sells test preparation and other books through retail channels.  The company was formerly known as The Washington Post Company and changed its name to Graham Holdings Company in November 2013. Graham Holdings Company was founded in 1877 and is based in Arlington, Virginia, US.

The Kuok Group engages in residential, commercial, and industrial property development activities in Asia. Its properties include hotels and resorts, and serviced apartments. It is also engaged in logistics and maritime operations. The company has a global strategic alliance with Drydocks World South-East Asia. The Kuok Group was formerly known as Kuok Brothers. It was founded in 1949 and is based in Johor Bahru, Malaysia.

The Kuok Group engages in residential, commercial, and industrial property development activities in Asia. Its properties include hotels and resorts, and serviced apartments. It is also engaged in logistics and maritime operations. The company has a global strategic alliance with Drydocks World South-East Asia. The Kuok Group was formerly known as Kuok Brothers. It was founded in 1949 and is based in Johor Bahru, Malaysia.

column5: Sinotruk (China National Heavy Duty Truck Group) (CNHTC)
column6: Sinotruk (China National Heavy Duty Truck Group) (CNHTC) (Sinotruk Group) develops, manufactures, and sells trucks, special trucks, buses, special vehicles, engines and engine units, auto parts, and special chassis products. It sells its products in China, as well as exports internationally. CNHTC was formerly known as Jinan General Auto Works Plant and changed its name in 2001. The company was founded in 1956 and is based in Jinan, China.

Aboitiz Equity Ventures, Inc., through its subsidiaries, engages in the power generation, distribution, and retail electricity supply; financial services; food manufacturing; real estate; infrastructure; and portfolio investments businesses in the Philippines. The company operates through Power, Banking & Financial Services, Food, Real Estate, and Infrastructure segments. It also engages in project management and projects involving civil works, industrial piping works, electro-mechanical works, and steel fabrication. The company was formerly known as Cebu Pan Asian Holdings, Inc. and changed its name to Aboitiz Equity Ventures, Inc. in December, 1993. Aboitiz Equity Ventures, Inc. was incorporated in 1989 and is based in Taguig, the Philippines.

Precision Auto Engineering manufactures automotive components, in particular, stainless steel fasteners which are used in all types of vehicles. The firm was founded in 1963 and is based in Ludhiana, India.

Hansae engages in the business of original equipment manufacturing and the export of garments. The company offers shirts, knits, lady's wear, casual clothes and other related products. It sells its products directly to buyers in the US. The company was founded in 1982 and is based in Seoul, South Korea.

POSCO engages in the manufacture and sale of steel products in Korea and internationally. It offers hot rolled steel, atmospheric corrosion resistant steel, cold rolled steel and titanium products. In addition, the company is involved in various other activities, including engineering and construction, steel work maintenance and machinery installation, computer hardware and software distribution, economic research and consulting, rental houses construction and management, energy and resource development, architecture, consulting, transporting, warehousing, and electricity generation. POSCO was established in 1968 and is headquartered in Seoul, South Korea. The frim previously operated as Pohang Iron and Steel.

column6: Lee & Man Paper Manufacturing, an investment holding company, manufactures and trades paper and pulp in China and Vietnam. It offers various pulp products, such as dissolved pulp for use in viscoce chemical fibre, bamboo fibre, glass paper, acetate fibre and refined rayon; unbleached bamboo kraft pulp for use in ecru life paper, environmental tableware and food bags; and bleached bamboo kraft pulp for use in tissue papers, fine papers, cigarette papers and cup papers. The company was founded in 1994 and is based in Kwun Tong, Hong Kong.

The Netherlands-based De Vierschaar is the holding firm for a number of companies. The mutual activities within the group include the provision of goods and property leasing. De Vierschaar is based in Ede Gold, Netherlands.
column36: Johan van den Ban, (Myanmar) managing director states that "for several years, De Heus Myanmar has had a sales warehouse in Mandalay to flexibly supply customers in the region. Based on growing demand, the identified high potential and our company's commitment to our local customers, we decided to invest in this new factory quite soon after opening our first factory back in October 2016. We hope that this new production facility will enable us to support the livestock farmers even better."

column6: Tama Home is engaged in the construction, architectural design, real estate, and insurance agency businesses in Japan. It primarily builds and sells houses for communities. The company was founded in 1998 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.
column38: Tama Home, Kakehasi Real Estate Group

column6: Mutsumi Special Alloy Industry Co., Ltd. manufactures automobile components. The company was founded in 1964 and is based in Machida, Japan.
GS Yuasa is a battery manufacturer. The company was founded in 1915 and is headquartered in Kyoto, Japan.
Auston Institute of Management is a Singapore-headquartered education company focused on engineering and project management titles. The company was founded in 1996.
column38: Myanmar Strategic Holdings, Auston Institute of Management

column6: Macan participates in all stages of ventures in a range of markets and sectors. The company forms deep partnerships with entrepreneurs to build their firms by committing its time, network and resources. Macan was founded in 2012 and headquartered in Singapore.
column36: Enrico Cesenni, founder, "The Board continues to seek new opportunities in this exciting market and is confident in its ability to identify areas of rapid growth."

column6: Kirin is a holding company engaged in the manufacture and sale of alcohol beverages and soft drinks. The company has four divisions. The alcohol beverage division is engaged in the manufacture and sale of beer, sparkling liquor and new alcohol beverage products, as well as the manufacture and sale of wines, the import of alcohol drinks, in addition to the automobile transportation and food industry-related engineering businesses. The beverage and food division manufactures and sells soft drinks, milk, dairy products, mineral water, fruit juice and seasonings. The pharmaceutical division is involved in the manufacture and sale of pharmaceutical products, as well as the research and development of pharmaceutical products. The company also operates a division which is engaged in the flower-related businesses. Kirin was founded in 1885 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.
Auston Institute of Management is a Singapore-headquartered education company focused on engineering and project management titles. The company was founded in 1996.
column38: Myanmar Strategic Holdings, Auston Institute of Management

column6: Yoma Strategic Holdings, an investment holding company, engages in real estate, agriculture, automotive, and luxury tourism businesses in Myanmar. The company develops gated community, residential, retail mall, serviced apartments, office towers, and landmark development projects. It is also involved in constructing residential units; rental of properties; property development and management, and design and architectural services; and advertising services, as well as operates quick services restaurants. Yoma Strategic was incorporated in 1962 and is headquartered in Singapore.
column36: Michael Rudenmark, head, automotive, yoma strategic," With our excellent range of products and early market entry we have a great opportunity to capture a large share of a motorcycle leisure market that is constantly growing in Myanmar."

column6: R&K Trading is an iron and steel trader. The firm was founded in 1992 and is based in Osaka, Japan.

FELDA Holdings, through its subsidiaries, engages in palm oil business. The company provides plantation development and management, oil palm processing, replanting, agricultural and plantation advisory, and cattle rearing services, as well as produces, refines, markets and packages oil based products. It is also involved in breeding and trading biological assets; animal food production; and fresh meat and carcass supply. FELDA Holdings was founded in 1988 and is based in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. The company is one of several private corporate entities launched by the Federal Land Development Authority (FELDA).

Kalbe Farma, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the production and development of pharmaceutical products. The company operates in four divisions: prescription pharmaceuticals, consumer health, nutritionals and distribution and logistics. The prescription pharmaceuticals division provides generic drugs, branded generics and licensed drugs. The consumer health division offers over-the-counter drugs and supplements and other preventive products, as well as energy drinks and healthy ready-to-drink products. The nutritionals division provides products for various age segments; and nutritional products for consumers with special medical needs. The distribution and logistics division distributes third party pharmaceuticals products, as well as operates an integrated chain of clinics that provide physician's general practice, pharmacies, laboratory and health mart services. Founded in 1966, the company is headquartered in Jakarta, Indonesia.
column36: Vidjongtius, president "I think Myanmar has great market potential as several Kalbe OTC drugs are already popular there,"

column6: European Plastics Window Company Ltd. manufactures and supplies windows and doors for customers worldwide. It offers uPVC products, which include tilt and turn inward opening windows, single sash entrance doors and internal doors, inward opening windows, balcony doors, outward opening windows, casement doors, UPVC partitions, sliding windows, sliding entrance doors, glass partitions, top hung windows, and folding entrance doors. The company also provides aluminum products, which include skylights, cobalt bulletproof doors, curtain walls, aluminum doors, and partitions; finger-joined wooden doors, natural wooden doors, composed wooden doors, and MDF and HDF wooden doors; automatic and rolling doors; glass products, including safety, tempered, double glazing, and pattern glass; and integrated blinds. In addition, it offers a range of services to customers from consultations, measurement, and design to production, installation, and maintenance work. Its products are used in various construction projects, such as office buildings, hotels, condominiums, and villas. The company offers its products through a network of distribution agents, as well as showrooms. European Plastics Window Company Ltd. was founded in 2002 and is based in Hanoi, Vietnam.

Muang Thai Life Assurance provides life insurance services to the people of Thailand. Its products and services include ordinary life insurance, salary savings life insurance, industrial life insurance, group life insurance, accidental and health insurance, loan and mortgage insurance. The company distributes its products through financial institutions, brokers, countrywide branches, a network of business alliances, and other business counterparts. Muang Thai Life Assurance Public Company Limited was formerly known as Muang Thai Life Assurance Co., Ltd. The company was founded in 1951 and is based in Bangkok, Thailand.

Matsuoka Corporation is a Japan-based fashion company, involved in the design and manufacturing of men's wear and woman's wear. The company was established in 1956, in Fukuyama and has since broadened its reach throughout Asia-Pacific and the US through its subsidiaries.

European Plastics Window Company Ltd. manufactures and supplies windows and doors for customers worldwide. It offers uPVC products, which include tilt and turn inward opening windows, single sash entrance doors and internal doors, inward opening windows, balcony doors, outward opening windows, casement doors, UPVC partitions, sliding windows, sliding entrance doors, glass partitions, top hung windows, and folding entrance doors. The company also provides aluminum products, which include skylights, cobalt bulletproof doors, curtain walls, aluminum doors, and partitions; finger-joined wooden doors, natural wooden doors, composed wooden doors, and MDF and HDF wooden doors; automatic and rolling doors; glass products, including safety, tempered, double glazing, and pattern glass; and integrated blinds. In addition, it offers a range of services to customers from consultations, measurement, and design to production, installation, and maintenance work. Its products are used in various construction projects, such as office buildings, hotels, condominiums, and villas. The company offers its products through a network of distribution agents, as well as showrooms. European Plastics Window Company Ltd. was founded in 2002 and is based in Hanoi, Vietnam.

Acudeen Technologies is an online technology platform that connects small and medium enterprises to financial institutions through invoice discounting. The company was founded in 2016 and is based in Makati, the Philippines.

Accor operates a chain of hotels worldwide. The company operates through HotelServices and HotelInvest segments. It operates a portfolio of luxury, upscale, midscale, economy, and budget hotels under the Sofitel, Pullman, MGallery, Grand Mercure, The Sebel, Novotel, Mama Shelter, Suite Novotel, Mercure, Adagio, Adagio Access, ibis, ibis Styles, ibis budget, hotelF1, Jo&Joe and Thalassa sea & spa brands. As of December 2015, the company operated approximately 510,000 rooms in 3900 hotels. The company was founded in 1967 and is based in Paris, France.

Yunnan Investment Holding Group is an industrial conglomerate operating through its subsidiaries in energy sources, transportation, urban construction, travelling, papermaking, finance, chemical, science and technology, and medical sectors. The company was formerly known as Yunnan Developing and Investment and changed its name to Yunnan Investment Holding Group in September, 2007. Yunnan Investment Holding Group was founded in 1997 and is headquartered in Kunming, China.

European Plastics Window Company Ltd. manufactures and supplies windows and doors for customers worldwide. It offers uPVC products, which include tilt and turn inward opening windows, single sash entrance doors and internal doors, inward opening windows, balcony doors, outward opening windows, casement doors, UPVC partitions, sliding windows, sliding entrance doors, glass partitions, top hung windows, and folding entrance doors. The company also provides aluminum products, which include skylights, cobalt bulletproof doors, curtain walls, aluminum doors, and partitions; finger-joined wooden doors, natural wooden doors, composed wooden doors, and MDF and HDF wooden doors; automatic and rolling doors; glass products, including safety, tempered, double glazing, and pattern glass; and integrated blinds. In addition, it offers a range of services to customers from consultations, measurement, and design to production, installation, and maintenance work. Its products are used in various construction projects, such as office buildings, hotels, condominiums, and villas. The company offers its products through a network of distribution agents, as well as showrooms. European Plastics Window Company Ltd. was founded in 2002 and is based in Hanoi, Vietnam.

Sido Muncul provides herbal medicines, cosmetics, and foods and beverages related to health in Indonesia and internationally. The company produces approximately 80 types of medicines consisting of ethical products, OTC products, food supplements, and medical herbs. Its products include Anacetine, a medicine to reduce fever; Combicitrine, a medicine for bacteries/worms removal; Berlosid, a medicine for gastric pains; Anabion multivitamins for children; Suprabion multivitamins for adults; and Telon Oil. The company also manufactures herbal extracts. In addition, it offers confectionary products, energy and health drinks, and other products. Further, the company is involved in commerce and land transportation activities. PT Industri Jamu dan Farmasi Sido Muncul Tbk is headquartered in Semarang, Indonesia, and was founded in 1940.

United Motor Works (Siam) Public Company Limited imports and distributes automotive service equipment. The company is the sole distributor of Briggs and Stratton diesel generator from the United States and "McKay" plough disc from Australia. The firm is based in Bangkok, Thailand and was founded in 1947.
column36: Atsushi Tomita, managing director,"Myanmar is our second largest market in Asean after Thailand because they are neighbouring countries. Sharing the growth in their mechanisation will benefit both countries,"

column6: Thai Beverage, together with its subsidiaries, produces and distributes alcoholic and non-alcoholic beverages in Thailand and internationally. The company operates through four segments: spirits, beer, non-alcoholic beverages, and food. It offers beer; spirits, including brown spirits, white spirits, brandy, Chinese herb spirits, and others; gin, vodka, and whisky; and non-alcoholic beverages comprising drinking water, soda water, electrolyte beverages, energy drinks, green tea, ready-to-drink coffee, and fruit flavoured drinks. Thai Beverage was incorporated in 2003 and is based in Bangkok, Thailand.

Harbor Star Shipping Services provides tugboat-based marine services in the Philippines. The company's services include harbour assistance services for public or open ports, as well as to private ports managed by corporations engaged in the oil and gas, power and mining industries, oil and chemical spill response services, diving and other marine services, ship repairs and fire fighting services. The company was formerly known as Seatows and changed its name in 1998. Harbor Star Shipping Services was incorporated in 1988 and is headquartered in Makati, Philippines.

Yamato Holdings provides delivery, logistics, home convenience, e-business, financial, and truck maintenance services. The company operates through six segments encompassing delivery, BIZ-logistics, home convenience, e-business, financial and auto-works. The company also provides highway transportation, personnel placement and JITBOX charter services. It has operations in Japan, North America, and internationally. The company was founded in 1919 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.

SHV Holdings engages in energy distribution and marketing, cash and carry wholesale, industrial services, and heavy lifting and transport businesses worldwide. The company supplies liquefied petroleum gas under the Primagaz, Calor Gas, Liquigas, Super Gas, Ipragaz, Supergasbras, Xiweigas, and Gaspol brand names; distributes liquefied natural gas and renewable energy; and invests in renewable energy solutions and LPG technology, such as micro combined heat and power, and fuel cells. It also invests in joint ventures that are involved in oil and gas exploration, development, and production activities primarily in the Netherlands and the United Kingdom. In addition, the company engages in cash and carry wholesale with 161 Makro stores in South America, which sells food and non-food products to small and medium-sized retailers, hospitality industry, and the institutional market; and provides heavy lifting and transport solutions in the petrochemical, power, offshore, marine, and civil engineering sectors. SHV Holdings was founded in 1896 and is based in Utrecht, the Netherlands.

Vietnam Dairy Products provides milk and dairy products in Vietnam and internationally. It processes, manufactures, and distributes milk cake, soya milk, fresh milk, refreshment drinks, bottled milk, powdered milk, nutritious powder, and other milk products. The company also offers yogurt, condensed milk, ice-cream, and cheese, as well as beverages, such as fruit juices, aloe vera drinks, bottled drinking water, salty lemonade, and tea. The company was founded in 1976 and is headquartered in Ho Chi Minh, Vietnam.
HUBS MK is based in South Korea.

Thonburi Healthcare Group Public Company Limited operates private hospitals in Thailand and internationally. The company operates through Medical Services, Healthcare Solution Provider Businesses, and Other Businesses segments. It offers services in various medical fields, including general medicine, pediatrics, obstetrics and gynecology, ophthalmology, otolaryngology, general surgery, bone and joint surgery, cardiology, neurology, dermatology, dentistry, and hemodialysis treatment; and management services for state hospitals, as well as for heart centers in the public and private sectors. The company also provides medical care services at patients' home; distributes medical supplies, devices, and equipment under the Adec, W&H, AO, Heraeus, Megagen, SAM, Melag, and Alpro brands; and develops hospital management software. As of June 30, 2016, it operated two Bangkok-based hospitals, such as Thonburi and Thonburi2 hospitals; and three provincial hospitals, including Rajyindee, Ubonrak Thonburi, and Sirivej Chanthaburi hospitals. Thonburi Healthcare Group Public Company Limited was founded in 1977 and is based in Bangkok, Thailand
column36: Boon Vanasin, chairman "Rising incomes and under-developed healthcare systems create opportunities for exponential growth in neighbouring countries,"

column6: PT Rajawali Nusantara Indonesia, through its subsidiaries, engages in agro-industry, and pharmaceuticals and medical device, as well as trading and distribution business. The company's agro-industry business activities include operating sugar factories in West Java, Yogyakarta, and East Java; and palm and tea plantations and processing factories. Its pharmaceuticals and medical devices activities comprise drug manufacturing, and syringes and condoms factory operations. In addition, the company engages in commerce distribution. PT Rajawali Nusantara Indonesia was founded in 1964 and is based in Jakarta, Indonesia.
Kuoni is a tourist travel company. Kuoni was founded in 1906 and is currently headquartered in Zurich, Switzerland.
